  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project to strengthen policies and programmes to prevent and remediate child labour in the Primark apparel supply chain</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The 3 year project is structured around the development of tools/protocols to implement Primark&#x2019;s Child Labour Code and Framework; the provision of training and awareness-raising, primarily for Primark staff. The PPP will identify and support systems to detect and remedy child labour and build capacity at different levels of the supply chain, including cotton growing communities. ILO-IPEC will support the development and implementation of Primark&#x2019;s Child Labour Code (CLC) and its Child Labour Framework (CLF). The PPP comprises two interlinked objectives, as follows: 1. Strengthened knowledge base on child labour in the apparel supply chain 2. Strengthened capacity to identify, prevent, and remediate child labour throughout Primark&#x2019;s apparel supply chains</narrative>
  </description>
